About Us

About Dr. Deobdut Choudharry

I am Dr. Deobdut Choudharry, a Palmistry and Numerology teacher with more than 19 years of experience in the field of occult sciences. I have completed my PhD from Maharishi College of Vedic Astrology, where I wrote my thesis on the Lifeline. Over the years, I have dedicated my work to understanding the deeper meanings hidden in our hands, numbers, and energies.

I am the founder and mentor of "The Prrophecy", where I teach students the true art of Palmistry and Numerology with clarity, logic, and spiritual understanding. Many students learn under my guidance, and I also share practical remedies that help people balance their life, mind, and destiny.

FAQs

Frequently Asked Questions

What services does Dr. Deobdut Choudharry offer?
We provide Palmistry consultations, Numerology sessions, professional courses, practical remedies, and personalised life guidance
How accurate are Palmistry and Numerology readings?
Our readings are based on ancient wisdom and years of experience. While accuracy can vary, we strive to provide insightful and meaningful guidance to help you make informed decisions.
Do you offer online classes?
Yes, we offer both online and offline classes to accommodate students from different locations and schedules.
Can beginners join your courses?
Absolutely! Our courses are designed to cater to all levels, from complete beginners to advanced practitioners. We provide comprehensive guidance at every step.
How long are the courses?
Course duration varies depending on the subject and level. We offer short-term workshops as well as comprehensive long-term programs. Please check our course details for specific durations.
What remedies do you provide?
We offer a wide range of practical remedies including gemstone recommendations, mantra chanting, yantra worship, and lifestyle modifications tailored to your specific needs and planetary positions.
How can I book a consultation?
You can book a consultation through our website, by calling our helpline, or by visiting our office. We offer both in-person and online consultation options.
Do you provide certificates after completing the course?
Yes, upon successful completion of our courses, students receive a certificate of completion that validates their knowledge and skills in the respective field.
What should I prepare before a consultation?
For Palmistry, bring clear photos of both palms. For Numerology, have your date of birth ready. For general consultations, prepare any specific questions or concerns you'd like to discuss.
Are your consultations and courses result-oriented?
Yes, our consultations and courses are designed to provide practical, actionable insights and remedies that can help you achieve positive changes in various aspects of your life.
